      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WONDERFULLY MADE (1) bolted in two back but couldn't repeat the dose last start in the Natasha when she couldn't sprint with her rivals. Fiore hops on board today and it wouldn't surprise to see them roll forward this time. Weights swing back in her favour today and she looks the one to beat in the Oaks. MASMELO (2) was positive last start and sprinted the best to score in the Natasha over 2200m. This looks to shape similarly for her this time around, though she does meet WONDERFULLY MADE worse at the weights. Should be handy and can repeat the dose. ADMIRE ASTRA (3) led them up in the Natasha but couldn't hold them off when dictating the tempo. The inside draw should see her close to the speed yet again and she's the next best. HEAVENLY RAPTURE (5) wasn't far away in the Natasha when closing from the back and is not to be discounted. POPPY'S ROSES (7) can be in the finish.",
